snippet.textDisplay:
I am not a QA but these are my findings when i went through the "Rangabati Remix version of coke studio". You guys could have done a review with a domain expert before releasing the product ;)


I have put timeline of video where issues are found:

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LY_rMXXuJp8&t=1m02s - http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LY_rMXXuJp8&t=1m14s : Laje Laje Lain jauchhi matha
Expected: Laje Laje nai jauchhe matha
Difference: "Nai" is the actual word for bending. I don't think "Lain" means same


http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LY_rMXXuJp8&t=1m16s - http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LY_rMXXuJp8&t=1m21s: O ranga, ranga ranga ranga ranga
Analysis: Ranga & Rangabati are two different things
Ranga is third gender and Rangabati is beutiful shy girl
Both cannot be same

Example: if in a english song you use "Shame Shame shame shame shame  shameless", how the meaning changes


http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LY_rMXXuJp8&t=1m32s - http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LY_rMXXuJp8&t=1m38s: Rani Tale suta male hela tu guntha
Expected: Ranir laagi suta mali helana guntha
Difference: its "Ranir lagi suta mali" means "A Ornamental thread For Queen" but in the video its "Rani tale Suta male" which means "Below the queen". And what she pronounced "mela hela tu guntha", i don't what is something exists like that.


http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LY_rMXXuJp8&t=1m55s - http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LY_rMXXuJp8&t=2m00s : E Aakhi asichhi jete sapana
Expected: i ankhin asichhe kete sapana
Difference: 
> Its "I" not "E" which changes the meaning
> Its "asichee" means "Has come", no word is there called "asichhi"
> Its "kete Sapana" not "Jete Sapana"



http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LY_rMXXuJp8&t=2m18s - http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LY_rMXXuJp8&t=2m29s : Maane Maali Mahakana go
Expected: Mane Mali Mahakana go
Difference:
> Its "Mane Mali Mahakana" means "Essence of Jasmine in mind". What she has sung means "Meaning is Essence of the Gardener"


http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LY_rMXXuJp8&t=2m36s - http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LY_rMXXuJp8&t=2m41s: Kede milana ahar milana chhana chhana hesi mana
Expected: kede milana aha mor dhana chhana chhana hesi mana
Difference:
> Its "Aha Mor dhana" means "The girl is getting called in a romantic way". But "ahar milana" don't who is meeting here


http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LY_rMXXuJp8&t=2m43s - http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LY_rMXXuJp8&t=2m50s: Dihi kandi gala Sangar Sirisha
Expected: bihi khanji gala sangar sarisa
Difference: Its "bihi Khanji gala" means "Fate created", but she pronounced "Dihi Kandi Gala" means "Body Cried"


http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LY_rMXXuJp8&t=2m50s - http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LY_rMXXuJp8&t=2m54s: tuhu tuhu maane kaari suruta
Expected: ubu tubu mane haee suruta
Difference: Its "ubu tubu mane haee suruta" means "Some one is recalling with a filled heart", but the line sang seems to me something gibbrish.

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LY_rMXXuJp8&t=4m40s- http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LY_rMXXuJp8&t=4m58s: She is dancing to the tune of Bande Utakala Janani (Odisha State Anthem) she is dancing


So every one who ever has went through must have got some sort of idea why all is happening.
1. Copy Right infringment
2. Meaning of the song is horrible. Its a murder of the lyrics.
3. Show some respect to the State Anthem
4. Many well know singers like Udit Narayan, Anuradha Podwal, Hari Haran they have never ate the lyrics. They have pronounced very well though being non-odia or nonn-sambalpuri.
5. When ppl suggested her in FB or sent eMail that she has not done justice and if possible make the necessary changes, She came out in her Fb page with a Arrogant Attitude.

All these wouldn't have been there(What is believe) if point #1 and #5 would have been taken care. Everyone want to see a renouned song with more matury and enhancement but not at the cost of its soul﻿
